{"source_key":"sha256-ea08d35f42d5530fbe92c80d4f5b27e9","record_index":14,"record_hash":"sha256:2d6eed3a1dfa7f2f3a7b425c435de2f8a6fd966503d44d2a95a2c5fd7abfcdc1","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:28:17.525Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 388149\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 2356\nOutput:\nlrwxr-xr-x  1 kiril  staff  79 May 24 17:20 agent-trail.md -> /Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md\n/Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md\n# Agent Trail\n\nAgent Trail is the review-adjacent product surface for captured agent sessions.\nIt is the page a reviewer opens from a pull request to understand the agent work\nbehind a change.\n\n## Working Name\n\nUse **Agent Trail** for now.\n\nGood future PR link text:\n\n- View Agent Trail\n- Explore Agent Trail\n- Agent Trail for this PR\n\nAvoid names like \"transcript\", \"audit log\", or \"provenance report\" for the\nproduct surface. The page may contain transcript records and provenance facts,\nbut the user-facing promise is simpler: follow the useful trail behind this\nchange.\n\n## Product Shape\n\nFor v1, a reviewer starts from a GitHub pull request URL and opens the matching\nGitButler-owned Agent Trail URL by replacing the host. The server builds or\nloads a generated snapshot for that public pull request.\n\nExplicit PR description links, bot comments, check-run details links, or GitHub\napp panels can come later as distribution channels. They are not required for\nthe first build.\n\nThe page lets the reviewer explore captured agent context related to the pull\nrequest:\n\n- prompts and requests from the human\n- assistant responses and claims\n- tool calls and tool results\n- tests and validation attempts\n- decisions and tradeoffs\n- follow-up questions\n- edge cases discussed or missed\n\nThis is not primarily a chat transcript viewer. Transcript records are the\nunderlying evidence, but the review experience should be organized around\nhelping a reviewer understand the change.\n\n## Core Question\n\nAgent Trail should answer:\n\n> What agent context helps me review this pull request?\n\nIt should not claim:\n\n> This agent session authored this pull request.\n\nThe language should stay evidence-based. Say that a session o\n[TRUNCATED]\n also gives reviewers a memorable gesture: replace\nthe forge domain with the Agent Trail domain.\n\n## Data Source\n\nAgent Trail should build on `but-agentlog` primitives:\n\n- durable project-scoped agent sessions\n- capture turns inside sessions\n- transcript records inside turns\n- observed branch, review, and change targets, though Agent Trail v1 consumes\n  only review and branch targets\n- verified related-session lookup\n- bounded turn and record hydration\n\n`but-agentlog` should remain the evidence layer. Agent Trail should live above\nit as a product-specific projection and browsing layer.\n\n## Public Projection Contract\n\nForge must render only an allowlisted public/read projection from\n`but-agentlog`. The projection is not a best-effort sanitizer over raw records;\nit is the contract for public web display.\n\nMinimum projection fields:\n\n- PR facts used for lookup: forge host, GitHub repository id, owner, repo, PR\n  number, base ref, head ref, and head SHA\n- snapshot facts: metadata ref OID, projection version, generated-at time, and\n  selected session/turn key digest\n- sessions: opaque public session handle, agent/provider label, timestamps,\n  match reasons, evidence tier, and related turn handles\n- turns: opaque public turn handle, timestamp, match reasons, evidence tier,\n  compact previews, and bounded drill-down handles\n- records for display: role/kind, timestamp when available, redacted bounded\n  text, command/tool label when available, validation outcome when derivable,\n  and source anchor handles\n- warnings: truncated output, weak branch-only evidence, no review-target match,\n  no validation found, stale or partial metadata, and projection limits reached\n\nForbidden public fields by default:\n\n- raw `source_record`\n- raw provider session ids\n- local transcript paths or local filesystem paths\n- hidden/system/developer messages\n- unbounded stdout/stderr or tool output\n- raw tool payloads that are not part of the allowlisted display record\n- raw session/turn keys in URLs, HTML, analytics, or public snapshot ids\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:28:17.525Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}